If Masipa grants leave then the appeal will be heard. If she turns it down then NPA can petition Supreme Court of Appeal in Bloemfontein.
Masipa must then decide if another judge could possibly come to a conclusion different to the one that she reached in the case.
To explain the process now - NPA will have to go back to Judge Masipa and ask her for 'leave to appeal' against her judgment and sentence.
#OscarPistorius NPA: The prosecutors are now preparing the necessary papers in order to be able to file within the next few days.
#OscarPistorius NPA: The merits, demerits of the NPA’s argument in this regard will become evident when we file papers for leave to appeal.

NPA: Adv Gerrie Nel and Andrea Johnson have been hard at work studying the judgement, researching  and also consulting with legal experts.

Double edged sword for police - have to be seen to be capable of responding to crime but can't be accused of preferential treatment.
Phiyega talks about 'global appeal' of this incident. Much like Oscar case, police need to be 'seen to be' responding and solving case.
#SenzoMeyiwa Phiyega now having to respond to suggestions that police are giving this case preferential treatment. Minefield for her.
Police say the cellphone stolen during #SenzoMeyiwa incident was not his and was on charge. Don't reveal who it belonged to.
Phiyega clearly describes #SenzoMeyiwa incident as 'house robbery'. Two suspects entered while a third remained outside. A shot was fired.

Police Commissioner Phiyega says there is a reward of R250 000 for information that will lead to arrest of #SenzoMeyiwa killers.

There are times when an incident shakes a country to its core causing collective devastation. Lucky Dube's death was one. Today is another.

#OscarTrial Masipa again summarising another example of case law. And then pauses for a drink of water, drawing this out.
#OscarTrial With jail time looking increasingly likely, there has been no reaction from Pistorius camp, sitting unmoved in front row.
#OscarTrial Judge Masipa finds that correctional supervision would not be appropriate for Oscar Pistorius.
#OscarTrial Masipa: The degree of negligence in this matter, the sentence as suggested by Vergeer, Maringa, not appropriate.
#OscarTrial In Voster case, a potential intruder would have had room to escape. In this case, only small bathroom.
#OscarTrial In Voster matter, the aim was to scare away the intruder. In this case it was to shoot the intruder.
#OscarTrial In Voster case, only one shot was fired and at an angle. In this case, four shots fired directly at the door.
#OscarTrial In Voster case, accused did not know there was someone behind the door. In this case, he did know someone was there.
#OscarTrial Masipa says facts in Voster are 'dissimilar' to those in this case. Number of important distinguishing features.
#OscarTrial Unfortunately not wise for Masipa to read out another sentence when people are so anxiously waiting for this one...
#OscarTrial Masipa is summarising the sentence in the Voster case - not Oscar's sentence.
#OscarTrial Oscar Pistorius has barely moved during the reading of the sentence. Staring directly ahead listening to Judge Masipa.
#OscarTrial Quotes from Voster sentence: The court should strive for balance, interests of society, accused and seriousness.'
#OscarTrial Masipa spending considerable time on the Voster case and the remorse of the accused in that matter.
#OscarTrial Masipa does pay special attention to Voster case - employer shot domestic worker's grandchild thinking it was an intruder.
#OscarTrial Masipa dismisses examples presented by defence of other incidents of shooting saying they are not 'on point'.
#OscarTrial Masipa giving very little away during her sentencing, leading us all one way and then another. Unlike her judgment.
#OscarTrial Masipa has a delicate balancing act to do here, as she clearly spells out now in her conclusion.
#OscarTrial Masipa: Hopefully this judgment on sentence will provide some closure for family.
#OscarTrial Masipa: The loss of life cannot be reversed. Nothing I say or do today can reverse what happened on 14 Feb 2013.
#OscarTrial Masipa: When deceased died she was full of hope for the future and full of life.
#OscarTrial Masipa: It is not wrong that the natural indignation of interested persons and community should receive some recognition.
#OscarTrial Masipa is not one to be influenced by the pressure of society and the tornado of public sentiment on this story.
#OscarTrial Masipa: As a country we have long moved from dark ages, an era of 'an eye for an eye'.
#OscarTrial Masipa: The general public may not even know the difference between justice and vengeance.
#OscarTrial Masipa on 'Interests of society' - 'Society can not always get what they want. Courts don't exist to win popularity contests'.
#OscarTrial Masipa: It is a fact that negative media reports about someone may affect someone's reputation and career.
#OscarTrial Court accepts as mitigating factor OP's conduct after the shooting, that he wanted Reeva to live.
#OscarTrial Significally, Masipa going through 'aggravating' issues around the actual shooting into the bathroom.
#OscarTrial Masipa moves to the seriousness of the offences - the shooting and the Tasha's incident.
#OscarTrial Judge says OP has inspired other people with disability worldwide. This cannot be ignored.
#OscarTrial Ironically, Masipa lists OP's mothers view that he should consider himself as able-bodied. This could be to his detriment now.
#OscarTrial Masipa says she felt unease at the emphasis placed on accused vulnerability. Says accused has excellent coping skills.
#OscarTrial Masipa: It would be a sad day if impression is created that there is one law for the poor and another for the wealthy.
#OscarTrial Masipa draws comparison to pregnant women being vulnerable and she would be sentenced if required.
#OscarTrial Masipa buys Nel's suggestion that if OP wanted a bench for his shower, it could be provided for him.
#OscarTrial Again Masipa chooses to accept evidence of Zac Modise. Seems prisons boss did right thing by coming to testify.
#OscarTrial Masipa: It became clear that the concern was not just about accused disability, but also that he needed treatment.
#OscarTrial Masipa doesn't want to usurp powers of Corr. Services. Individuals can always approach court to seek redress.
#OscarTrial Masipa says she has no doubt that correctional services will be able to accommodate Oscar Pistorius.
#OscarTrial Critical finding by Judge Masipa - chooses to accept prisons boss evidence over that of social worker Vergeer.
#OscarTrial Masipa says if  given custodial sentence - it will not be first time correc. services has to deal with person with disability.
#OscarTrial Masipa says she has no question in accepting evidence of acting prisons boss Zac Modise as reliable and credible.
#OscarTrial Masipa on Vergeer: Sketchy, outdated, uninformed.
#OscarTrial Masipa says Vergeer's evidence was 'slapdash, dissapointing and had negative impact on her credibility as witness'.
#OscarTrial Masipa: I was not impressed at all by Vergeer as a witness. She did not inspire confidence despite experience.
